        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 12 at 7:59PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 758 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Broad River Campground to near Beall Springs, and
moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Frequent cloud to ground lightning and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. If you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by
lightning. Heavy rain may cause temporary street flooding
especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Washington, Warrenton, Tignall, Norwood, Camak, Ficklin, Cadley,
Lundberg, Delhi, Beall Springs, Metasville, Holliday Park, Floral
Hill, Aonia, Danburg, Rocky Creek Fire Dept., Reese, and Mesena.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.  Electrical
appliances should not be used unless in an emergency. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
